review_blob: UPDATED: MAR 25, 2016

New "red ale" of Gara Guzu includes honey & beetroot! Amazing. Especially its head looks like silk and reminds me Guinness! A semi bitter finish gives that beer a special character. I really enjoyed it...Gara Guzu keeps on pioneering turkish craft beer world...
Ive tried many hellenic beers, each of them were really cool but this is not a beer, this is lemonade! Just like mariachi beer that the girls drink in summertime; the girls who hate beer!

330 ml bottle from the Rind Store in Kadikoy / Istanbul... It was shocking to see a beer in Turkey from a microbrewery! That microbrewery is new in Mugla (Aegean side of Turkey) and their amber ale is pretty well! A promising step for Turkish beer culture. You better try it!

330 ml botlle from Hellas... Foam is unbelievable! Its huge and doesnt leave you until your last sip. Fresh grass aroma promises a quality beer and indeed; semi-bitter taste proves that. Palate is not so strong, maybe average but OK. I can call it maybe, one of the "secret gem"s of Hellas...

Bottle at the United pub in Istanbul. Appearance is a little ordinary but fresh citrus aroma promises a good ale. Sweet notes of rose syrup but the keyword for this beer is wonderful "bitterness". A long bitter finish, a real wild river! Cool...
A full bodied pilsner in hellas. Youll feel youre drinking a real beer. Not like the marketing stuff...

when you open the bottle, a fresh pineapple flavor welcomes you. dark golden color and a little cloudy body looks great. first i thought its a little sweet but then the malty / bitter taste is dominant at all. 
these brewdog beers take me back to my childhood with their "haribo like" tastes but anyway, finish is acceptably strong and juicy.

330 ml bottle in turkey... very warm sourcherry flavour welcomes you when you open the bottle and strong bittersweet / sourcherry explosions follow you until you see end of the beer very quickly! long lasting finish reminds me my childhood years wasted with cough syrup (!) but anyway, very charismatic ale...

another weak beer from efes pilsen... just like efes pilsen says, its "easy to drink" because its as fresh as water especially when you drink it very cold. efes (turkeys most selling beer) adds sugar to its beer but this version is sugar free. thats only reason to buy it.
330 ml bottle in turkey. a classic ale with a very fine / bitter taste. finish is also bitter and long. a very good choice if you like ale!
a very fresh beer to drink anywhere - anytime. for sure its not a 3th class beer and its smell is very refreshing but!... finally its like water! use it as a perfume :)

500 ml bottle. aroma is not bad, its a little floral and promises a good beer... but just like soda, its not easy to drink! anyway, light bitter taste and finish are ok. better drink at pubs in thessaloniki if you can find draught kaiser.
no matter tap or can. great quality if you like lager. it doesnt look like " a fancy beer", it doesnt smell like "a complex beer" but simply, its a very reel beer!

500 cl. bottle. smells like soap but its pretty fresh. i always think that weissbier shouldnt mean "banana", ok. but if were talkin about franziskaner kristallklar, its hard to say a weissbier. maybe its a "light banana soda" that looks like a very pure and clean lager.
50 ml can. it feels like youre opening a guinness; appearence is perfect! taste is clean. not complex but also not tiring. that means finish is a little weak. a beer you can drink anywhere, anytime.
330 ml bottle. a great pilsner. soon as you open the bottle you can smell wild flowers. colour and taste also tell you that youre drinking a special beer! a good choice if you can find...
50 cl bottle from greece. a real classic. maybe not the best wheat beer but its absolutely fine. banana aroma is a problem or a fact (?) for all that kind of beers. and also good with bockwurst.
A miracle and a magical pilsner! first it charms you with beautiful aromas and then you realize that you are drinking a "real beer".
Fresh but a weak beer. Good price is only reason to buy it. for sure there are better beers in hellas.
If you can?t find german beers, this one is a good choice in turkey. It?s a lager but you can think you?re drinking a good hefe weizen.
